<HEADLINE>
<P>
PUTTING ELECTRIC CARS ON THE ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your editorial overlooks a compelling argument for massive investment in 
freeways and highways as a solution to regional transportation needs. 
</P>
<P>
Automobiles, replaced every few years, are a "renewable resource." They can 
quickly accommodate future technical breakthroughs in energy-efficient and 
low-pollution power plants. The flexibility and productivity provided by the 
automobile-based personal rapid transit system is thus preserved. 
</P>
<P>
Huge investments in mass transit sufficient to reduce automobile travel will 
forever lock us into slow inflexible transportation, causing unacceptable 
losses in productivity and quality of social life. 
</P>
<P>
WALTER BREWER 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Palos Verdes 
</P>
</TEXT>
