<HEADLINE>
<P>
PUTTING ELECTRIC CARS ON THE ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I'm afraid you gave a very misleading and false impression of electric cars in 
your editorial. 
</P>
<P>
Here are the facts: 
</P>
<P>
1) Although Detroit may not be producing electric cars, our small company is 
currently producing and selling them! 
</P>
<P>
2) Our electric cars are not cumbersome, quite the contrary, they're fun to 
drive. 
</P>
<P>
3) Our electric cars can easily run up freeway ramps and even maintain freeway 
speeds. 
</P>
<P>
4) 90% of all second-car driving is under 21 miles per day, making today's 
electrics feasible for about half of all driving needs. 
</P>
<P>
5) Our cars are affordable ($10,000 to $15,000) and available for purchase now. 
</P>
<P>
GARY STARR 
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Officer 
</P>
<P>
Rohnert Park, Calif. 
</P>
