<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hosts With the Most: Exiled New York Yankees owner George Steinbrenner, "All My 
Children" star Susan Lucci, musician Paul Simon and film actors Patrick Swayze, 
Christian Slater and Tom Hanks will be among the guest hosts this season for 
"Saturday Night Live," producer Lorne Michaels announced. . Steinbrenner's date 
on the show is Oct. 20. Kyle MacLachlan, who plays FBI agent Dale Cooper on 
ABC's "Twin Peaks" will host "SNL's" 16th season premiere Sept. 29, with Sinead 
O'Connor the musical guest. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
