<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092090-0018 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 278564 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 20, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part F; Page 2; Column 1; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
53 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gubernatorial News Hour: Robert MacNeil of PBS' "The MacNeil/Lehrer NewsHour" 
will talk to California's candidates for governor. MacNeil's conversations with 
Dianne Feinstein and Pete Wilson will air Oct. 24 at 8 p.m. on KCET Channel 28. 
The program will be offered to other PBS stations in California. BETH KLEID 
</P>
