Photo, Crash Course in Safety: Inglewood officials simulated a plane crash on 
the border with Los Angeles to measure how prepared area emergency response 
agencies are for such a disaster. More than 20 area police and fire departments 
participated, along with Warren Lane Elementary School students. At top, 
students are brought from the classroom "crash site" for transport to a nearby 
hospital. Student Dejean Cole's stretcher is tagged with his "condition" of 
possibly having a concussion. At the command post at Hollywood Park, below, 
