<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An apparently drug-related shooting left one man dead and another man injured 
in Southeast San Diego, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Just before 8 p.m. Tuesday, police were dispatched to 29th Street and Imperial 
Avenue, where they found a man shot in the head lying dead in a gutter, Lt. Dan 
Berglund said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Frank Eli Heard, 24, of Southeast San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
About a quarter of a block away, another man was found with gunshot wounds to 
his chest and leg. 
</P>
<P>
Victor Corder, 26, also of Southeast San Diego underwent surgery and was listed 
in stable condition Wednesday at UC San Diego Medical Center, a hospital 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Three men apparently confronted the two, who were standing next to a car on 
29th just north of Imperial and got into an argument, Berglund said. The three 
drew guns and started shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Corder, wounded, ran down the street. The three men beat up Heard before 
shooting him in the head while he was on the ground, Berglund said. 
</P>
<P>
No drugs were found at the scene and the three assailants scattered in 
different directions after the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
