<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GANG MEMBERS HURT IN SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities say two gang members from Carson were wounded Sunday night when 
rival gang members from Harbor City sprayed a restaurant's parking lot with 
gunfire. No one else was injured in the 8:30 shooting in Harbor City. 
</P>
<P>
"It could have turned into a real gun battle," Los Angeles Police Detective Kim 
Wierman said. 
</P>
<P>
Wierman said Romeo Anos, 19, and Alexander Jacinto, 20, both identified as gang 
members, were felled by gunfire as they left the Beef Bowl restaurant at 1111 
W. Pacific Coast Highway. The shooting occurred minutes after one of the men 
had crossed out the name of a Harbor City gang from the men's room wall at the 
restaurant, Wierman said. 
</P>
<P>
Anos was hit in the back by one of 10 to 15 bullets fired in the incident. The 
bullet passed through his chest and lodged in his chin, police said. He was 
listed in stable condition at Harbor-UCLA Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
Jacinto, shot in the right ankle and hip, was treated for his wound at the 
medical center, Wierman said. 
</P>
<P>
No suspects are in custody. 
</P>
</TEXT>
