</P>
<P>
The unit will be called Time Warner Publishing Inc., and it will oversee Time 
Inc. Magazine Co., with about $2 billion in revenue a year, and Time Inc. Book 
Co., with more than $1 billion in annual revenue. Brack, 53, will be chairman 
of the new unit while retaining his titles as chairman, president and chief 
executive of the magazine company. Its publications include Time, Life, Sports 
Illustrated, People and Fortune. 
</P>
</TEXT>
