<P>
Mustang Ranch Seized: The Mustang Ranch, one of the world's best-known 
brothels, has been seized by the Internal Revenue Service and may soon be 
operated by a federal bankruptcy court. 
</P>
<P>
After years of negotiations over millions in unpaid taxes owed by owner Joe 
Conforte, the IRS obtained an order from the bankruptcy court in Reno to begin 
liquidating the 105-room brothel. Jerri Coppa, the bankruptcy trustee assigned 
by the court to sell the property, said she planned to supervise the operation 
of the business until it could be sold. Coppa said when she arrived at the 
ranch, which is located about six miles east of Reno, she found the 
establishment closed and the employees scattered. 
