<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: LOS ANGELES; 
</P>
<P>
ARTS COUNCIL PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Arts Council, a nonprofit organization dedicated to filling 
cultural needs in the city, has created several programs for local artists who 
are not represented by commercial galleries. 
</P>
<P>
Citing the lack of venues for little-known artists, the council has invited 
local artists to submit samples of their work for possible display in its 
programs. 
</P>
<P>
These include art-in-business spaces, which places art in and near where people 
work; an annual art auction; a sculpture walk; an upcoming exhibit featuring 
women artists from culturally diverse backgrounds, and a gallery space in the 
Century City Shopping Center. 
</P>
<P>
Artists who would like to be considered should submit a minimum of 10 slides 
and a resume to the council at 10250 Santa Monica Blvd., Suite 194, Los Angeles 
90067. For further information, call (213) 552-3539. 
</P>
</TEXT>
