WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
PREFERENTIAL PARKING OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday night adopted two ordinances establishing 
preferential parking zones within Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
One of the ordinances limits parking to a maximum of two hours between 9 a.m. 
and 6 p.m. Monday through Saturday, except by permit, on Dorchester Avenue 
between Exposition Boulevard and Delaware Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
The council also voted to expand the preferential parking zone in the Ocean 
Park area to include Bicknell Avenue between 3rd and 4th streets. For those 
without a permit, parking is limited to a maximum of two hours between 9 a.m. 
and 10 p.m. and prohibited between 10 p.m. and 2 a.m. 
</P>
