<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092090-0085 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 278791 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 20, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Glendale; Part J; Page 10; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
116 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DRUNK DRIVER GETS $1,500 FINE, PROBATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Glendale woman convicted of driving with a blood-alcohol level more than five 
times the legal definition of drunk was put on probation last week and fined 
about $1,500. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale Municipal Judge Barbara Lee Burke on Friday ordered Cathylynne Johnson 
to serve three years probation, pay fines and restitution and attend an 
Alcoholics Anonymous program. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, 28, pleaded no contest last Wednesday to two misdemeanor charges of 
driving with a blood-alcohol level higher than 0.08% -- the state's legal 
definition of drunk -- and fleeing the scene of an accident. 
</P>
<P>
She was arrested March 27 after she ran into another car on Verdugo Road near 
Towne Avenue and then left the scene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
