<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DOCTOR IN SEX CASE SUED BY STATE MEDICAL 
BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Medical Board of California filed suit Wednesday seeking to revoke the 
license of a Brentwood physician while he awaits trial on charges that he 
sexually assaulted at least four female patients. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Yahya Joe Lavi was arrested in July for allegedly raping or molesting four 
women who had been referred to him for examinations related to Worker's 
Compensation benefits, said Deputy Atty. Gen. Nancy Ann Stoner. 
</P>
<P>
The 52-year-old orthopedist "has sexually abused four of his patients, and he 
has falsely represented his qualifications in medical reports," said the 
lawsuit filed in Los Angeles Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
Lavi could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
The doctor has other offices in Los Angeles, Long Beach, Covina, Pasadena, 
Panorama City and Lancaster. The alleged sexual assaults occurred at offices in 
Panorama City and Los Angeles, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
