<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNLV'S TARKANIAN TO VISIT ANTELOPE VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRENDAN HEALEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jerry Tarkanian, Nevada Las Vegas basketball coach, will return to the Antelope 
Valley today for a visit, more than three decades after he coached the 1958 
Antelope Valley High basketball team to a 4-9 record. 
</P>
<P>
It was his only season at the school and his only losing season as a coach, but 
now he has plenty of reasons to return. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley College, the local junior college, has been nicknamed UNAV 
because of its ties to Tarkanian and the UNLV basketball program. 
</P>
<P>
Tarkanian will attend the college's basketball class/practice from 3 p.m. to 5 
p.m. and likely will have a Shark's eye on 6-foot-5 sophomore swingman J. R. 
Rider. 
</P>
<P>
Newton Chelette, Antelope Valley's basketball coach, is a former Tarkanian 
assistant, and Chelette sent his star player, former Taft High standout Dedan 
Thomas, to UNLV this season. 
</P>
<P>
Tarkanian's son George was hired last month as a political science teacher at 
Antelope Valley College. BRENDAN HEALEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
