<HEADLINE>
<P>
RALSTON TO CLOSE A PET FOOD PLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ralston-Purina Co. said it will close its pet food plant in Mechanicsburg, Pa., 
in late November or early December, continuing a streamlining effort. 
</P>
<P>
The facility, one of eight Ralston pet food plants in the United States, opened 
in 1970 and makes a complete line of dry foods for dogs and cats. Production 
will be shifted to other plants, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
The date of the closing will depend on production schedules, a company 
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
