<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: COMPTON; 
</P>
<P>
TRASH HAULER'S REQUEST FOR RATE HIKE TERMED EXCESSIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With one member absent Tuesday night, the Compton City Council decided to put 
off a decision on whether to raise residential trash collection rates. Mayor 
Walker R. Tucker has been ill and unable to attend council meetings this month. 
</P>
<P>
The city's trash hauler, Murcole Inc., is seeking a rate increase of 17.16%. 
That would push the current monthly rate from $11.32 per residence to $13.26. 
</P>
<P>
The city staff told the council in a memo that the request is excessive because 
the consumer price index has risen only 4.9% and dumping fees at landfills have 
not gone up enough to justify such a high rate hike. 
</P>
<P>
The city staff is recommending that the rate be raised to $11.94, which would 
be a 5.5% increase. The council is scheduled to take up the issue again at its 
meeting next Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
