<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: MONROVIA; 
</P>
<P>
GROUP GETS OPTION ON LAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council agreed Tuesday to give the Trust for Public Land, a nonprofit 
group, the option to buy 1,200 acres of city land in Sawpit Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Trust for Public Land will have two years to decide 
whether to buy the hillside property for $648,000, or about $540 an acre. The 
trust, based in San Francisco, buys property and transfers it to such agencies 
as the U.S. Forest Service for permanent preservation as open space or for 
recreational use, City Atty. Richard J. Morillo said. 
</P>
<P>
Monrovia sold 635 acres of land in the foothills above Duarte to the same group 
in 1987 for $320,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
