<P>
OFTEN MY LOVE: One of the most-performed songs in history is "Never My Love," 
made a hit in 1967 by the Association, whose members, brothers Larry and Del 
Ramos, still live in Orange County. . . . According to music giant BMI, the 
song's been performed 5 million times. "We did 192 dates last year, and we have 
to do that tune," says Del. "That's what they come to hear from us." Zan Dubin 
and Lucy Chabot 
