<TEXT>
<P>
CHEERS: Amy Apodaca didn't wait for legal action when she was suspended Friday 
from the Dana Hills High School pep squad because of a haircut school officials 
considered extreme. 
</P>
<P>
The popular high school senior started a petition right away, and by midweek 
she had about 200 signatures. Apodaca said she didn't have time or reason to 
give it to administrators, since she was reinstated Wednesday (B3). "Right 
now," she says, "our main concern is football and basketball." Zan Dubin and 
Lucy Chabot 
