<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
YRIZAR'S GOAL GETS UCI PAST NAVY IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pablo Yrizar scored with three seconds remaining in the game to give UC Irvine 
a 13-12 nonconference water polo victory Wednesday over Navy at Annapolis, Md. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine, which is ranked No. 7 in the country and has a 3-3 record, saw a 7-4 
halftime lead diminish as Navy outscored the Anteaters, 5-3, in the third 
quarter. Navy's Elton Parker scored to tie the score at 12-12 with 53 seconds 
remaining before Yrizar's winning goal. 
</P>
<P>
Skylar Putnam scored four goals, Steve Gill had three and Yrizar two for 
Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 2, UC Irvine 0 -- Leo Ronces and Toby Taitano scored for San Diego 
(5-0-3) at Irvine (2-5-1). Mike Gartlan had six saves for Irvine. 
</P>
