</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DENVER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If Denver is awarded a National League baseball franchise for 1993, the team 
will be known as Colorado and a fan contest will determine the nickname. 
</P>
<P>
The use of Denver in the title has been ruled out, and it's not considered 
likely that the nickname of Bears will be used because of marketing conflicts 
with the NFL's Chicago Bears. Several fan groups, however, have been attempting 
to drum up support to keep the Bears' name, which has been associated with 
Denver's minor-league baseball teams for most of this century. 
</P>
<P>
Denver was removed as a possibility because the prospective owners want to send 
the signal it will be a regional team, not the city's team. 
