<HEADLINE>
<P>
BH JAMBABY AFTER HER SIXTH WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Black Hills Ranch's B H Jambaby will be looking for her fifth career win 
Friday night at Los Alamitos as she tackles Colross Racing Inc. and Michael 
Schwartz's Kitty Spirit and seven others in the $25,000 California Platinum 
Series Final for pacing fillies and mares. 
</P>
<P>
In post position order, the field for the $25,000 Friday night main event, 
which is carded as the eighth race: Cheechita Princess, Joe Anderson in the 
race bike; Cappuccine, Robert Sleeth; Black On Black, Robert Rosen; Kitty 
Spirit, Ross Croghan; La Boulangere, Todd Ratchford; Bread To Shine, Rick 
Plano; Equus Ronni, Ed Hensley; B H Jambaby, Rick Kuebler, and Miss Boom Boom. 
</P>
<P>
Also on the Friday night card is a $20,000 distaff pacing Free For All. The 
Gusty Stable's Doodlin will be gunning for her third straight victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
